channel.title: Games you're looking forward to the most
channel.description: Hey all, I was enjoying the thread about cancelled games quite a bit and i figured i'd create a thread doing the exact opposite. So, like the title suggests, what games are you looking forward to the most? For me, i am looking forward to a new TPS in the Warhammer 40k universe called Warhammer: Space Marine. I am also terribly excited for a new MMOFPS coming out by the creators of EvE Online. The game is called Dust 514 and looks pretty awesome from the gameplay footage i've seen so far.

item.dc:creator: xalener
item.description:
Can’t be bothered to make my own so I’ll edit the last guy’s

Mortal Kombat
Duke
Half-Life 2: Episode 3/ HL3 (HAHAHAHAHAAAAA!!!)
Deus Ex: Human Revolution
Portal 2
Next Bungie Game
Uncharted 3
Battlefield 3
Bioshock: Infinite
Aliens: colonial marines
Alice: madness returns

aaaand Gears 3 kinda. I always liked the core gameplay, but the last game was a broken piece of trash and the first one got a bit boring (though not bad to just pick up every now and then). Since this next one is gonna have a beta, I can trust that it will play a hell of a lot better than the last two. Plus this one has an actual color pallete, making it a stand out in shooters this year.

These next couple of years are going to be fucking BUSY.

item.title: Games you're looking forward to the most
item.dc:creator: Orpheon
item.description:
Oblivion was pretty fun to play once. Don’t think I’ll ever play it again though. I know some people who have spent hundreds of hours playing it though, modding the crap out of it and replaying everything and maxing stats and what not. Open world “make-your-own-adventure” games just don’t tickle my fancy all that much, so when the main quests were over, I was pretty much done. Can’t stand MMOs either. I’ll probably get Skyrim on the same time table I got Oblivion - 5 years later, when it’s $10 on Steam.

Read full topic
